{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Teleprompter","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Teleprompter"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I have a scene that takes my record output and flips it horizontally. I preview"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this on a second monitor that is a small LCD panel under a teleprompter."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The flip filter compensates for the mirror (and the fact that neither my"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"panel nor macOS will do a screen "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"flip"}]},{"type":"text","text":", though both do screen rotations)."}]},{"anchor":"Setup","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Setup"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I use the same, single “Teleprompter” scene for recorded and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interactive sessions.  I enable depending on use."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For recording, the only source is the “SurfaceTiled” scene that I"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"manage with OBSurface."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For videoconferences, there is a collection of captured and filtered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"windows."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each source is given a “flip horizontal” transform to adapt to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"teleprompter mirror."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The scene is then displayed on the teleprompter panel using either a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fullscreen or windowed Scene Projector."}]},{"anchor":"Video","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Video"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{